    "short_description": "KC's most flavorful corridor — craft beer, tacos, and coffee along Southwest Blvd.",
    "long_description": "Southwest Boulevard is one of Kansas City's most underrated and delicious streets, a diverse strip that blends longstanding Hispanic restaurants and taquerias with craft beer institutions and specialty coffee roasters. \n\nStart your morning at The Roasterie Factory Cafe, where Kansas City's beloved local roaster serves exceptional coffee in their flagship cafe near the roasting facility. A short walk up the boulevard brings you to Boulevard Brewing Company, the iconic KC craft brewery with a welcoming taproom and tours. \n\nFor tacos, you have two great options: Tacos El Gallo for no-frills, authentic street-style tacos that locals swear by, and Margarita's Southwest Boulevard for a sit-down Mexican meal with strong margaritas and a lively atmosphere. \n\nKC Wheel rounds out the itinerary with wood-fired pizza and a curated bar in a relaxed neighborhood setting. Southwest Blvd rewards slow exploration — it's the kind of street where you find something new every visit.",
